Thanks for catching that! 🙏

The streaming behavior of `usageMetadata` isn't really spelled out in the Vertex AI / Gemini docs — it just happens that the API sends a `usageMetadata` field on most chunks, mostly with empty or partial values, with the actual totals landing in the final chunk. So we were yielding indiscriminately.

Pushed a fix in the spirit of your remark: only yield a `TokenUsage` when the chunk carries an actual `totalTokenCount > 0`. Added a regression test covering empty + partial intermediate chunks alongside the populated one.

Would be happy if you could re-run the example to confirm you now see exactly one usage event instead of seventeen. 🙂
